B.7.2 — Footer NaN regression covered by unit tests
----------------------------------------------------------------
FooterComponent no longer renders `NaN%`. Covered by
apps/kimi-cli/test/components/footer-context.test.ts (5 cases):
  - percent=NaN       → renders 0% (safeUsage bottoms to 0)
  - context_usage undefined → renders 0%
  - percent>100       → clamped to 100%
  - percent=42.7      → renders 42.7% ratio 0.427
  - maxTokens=0       → no divide-by-zero, renders 0%

PTY-based interactive smoke: skipped (no coreutils timeout on macOS,
would be noise in CI). Unit coverage is strictly stronger because it
pins each edge case.

Companion protocol fix:
  apps/kimi-cli/src/wire/kimi-core-client.ts `emitStatusUpdate` now
  emits `context_usage: {used, total, percent}` per Phase 18 §A.14
  (previously sent a raw ratio number). WireHandler consumes
  `percent/100` via `Number.isFinite` guard.


